'''''Booze, Broads and Beelzebub''''' is the second studio album by [[Chrome Division]]. The band announced that they had finished recording the album on [[January 15]], [[2008]] on their [[MySpace]] blog,<ref name="blog1">{{cite web |url= http://blog.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view&friendID=65152680&blogID=347844772|title= New Album Recorded|accessdate=2008-02-04 |date= [[2008]]-[[01-15]]|work= Official blog|publisher= [[Chrome Division]]}}</ref> and announced the title and the planned release date of [[July 8]], [[2008]] on their blog on [[May 14]], [[2008]],<ref>{{cite web |url= http://blog.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view&friendID=65152680&blogID=394063894|title=Release date and title for New Album |accessdate=2008-05-15 |date= [[2008]]-[[05-14]]|work= Official blog|publisher=[[Chrome Division]]}}</ref> which was picked up on by [[heavy metal]] news sources.<ref>{{cite news |first= Peggy|last= Tsui|title= Chrome Division to Release New Album in July|url=http://www.metalunderground.com/news/details.cfm?newsid=36629|publisher= MetalUnderground.com|date= [[2008]]-[[05-14]]|accessdate=2008-05-15}}</ref> The album took seven days to record at Studio Fredmann in [[Gothenburg]], starting on [[January 7]], [[2008]].<ref name="blog1"/> Before either of the blog announcements, bassist Bj<U+00F6>rn Luna said in an interview that Chrome Division's next album would be released on [[Nuclear Blast]], explaining that the band have a three album contract with the label,<ref name="Eagle">{{cite web |url= http://www.metaleagle.com/interviews.php?action=show&id=143&PHPSESSID=8993a87adfc69bf4|title= Chrome Division- Interview with Bj<U+00F6>rn Luna|accessdate=2007-08-20 |last= Smirnioti|first= Marilena|publisher= MetalEagle.com}}</ref> and [[Blabbermouth.net]] confirmed that the album would be released on Nuclear Blast.<ref name="BM">{{cite news |title= Dimmu Borgir Frontman's Chrome Division To Release Sophomore Album In July|url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=96987 |publisher= [[Blabbermouth.net]]|date= [[2008]]-[[05-14]]|accessdate=2008-05-15 }}</ref> Though no tracklisting has been announced, the band did say that 12 tracks were recorded at Studio Fredmann,<ref name="blog1"/> and it has been revealed that one of these is a cover of a [[ZZ Top]] song.<ref name="BM"/> According to the band, the music will be "a bit more varied than on ''Doomsday Rock 'n Roll''. A bit more metal, more fast stuff, but still the basics in filthy rock 'n' roll."<ref name="BM"/>

